              },
              "free_text": [
                " The accelerator voltage was adjusted to pro-",
                " duce Li-7(p,n) neutrons only with energies between",
                " 10 and 60 keV, all of them emitted into a cone with",
                " 60 degrees opening angle."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Three metallic, uncanned disc samples of Fe-56 (99.93%",
                " pure in Fe-56) were used. The thicknesses were",
                " 0.15, 0.3 and 0.6 mm.",
                " The reference sample was a gold disc, 0.25 mm thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of flight techniques were used to",
                " distinguish between neutrons and captured photons.",
                " The primary flight path was 7.6 to 8 cm long and",
                " about half as long as the distance between the",
                " sample and the detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MOXR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A Moxon-Rae detector. The detector response",
                " to a pure scatterer was checked with a graphite",
                " sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
